\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b sicula} ({\i S. depressa} Biv.): Densely caespitose; flowering stems 5-15(-25) cm, with c. 2 pairs of linear-oblanceolate leaves, c. 2- to 8-flowered. Inflorescence-branches and pedicels densely glandular-pubescent. Calyx densely glandular-pubescent with rather stout hairs.{\i  Sicilia; Sardegna}.
