\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b intermedia} (Simmler) Chater,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  69}: 52 (1964) ({\i S. intermedia} Simmler; incl. {\i S. haussknechtii} Simmler): Like subsp. ({\b a}) but usually less densely caespitose; flowering stems (5-)10-50 cm, more leafy, 1- to 30-flowered; inflorescence-branches and pedicels less densely pubescent, usually glandular; calyx less densely pubescent with more slender hairs, eglandular. •{\i  S. Jugoslavia, N. Greece, Albania}.
