\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. S. ocymoides }L., {\i Sp. Pl}. 409 (1753). Much-branched perennial with procumbent or ascending hairy stems. Lower leaves subspathulate to ovate-lanceolate, obtuse; upper narrower, acute. Inflorescence lax, spreading; pedicels and calyx glandular-pubescent. Calyx 7-12 mm, teeth obtuse. Petal-limb 3-5 mm, pale purplish. 2n = 28. •{\i  S.W. & S.C. Europe; N. & C. Italy.} Au Co Ga Ge He Hs It Ju Sa [Cz].
