\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. S. chlorifolia }(Poiret) G. Kunze,{\i  Ind. Hort. Lips. }{\b 1846}: 4 (1846) ({\i Cyathophylla chlorifolia} (Poiret) Bocquet & Strid). Glabrous, glaucous annual; stems 8-15 cm, procumbent or ascending. Basal leaves in a rosette, ovate or broadly spathulate, obtuse; cauline perfoliate, ovate to orbicular. Inflorescence capitate, of 2-6 shortly pedicellate flowers; involucre bowl-shaped, entire. Calyx 9-13 mm, with short, triangular teeth. Petals about equalling the calyx, pink. Seeds c. 12 mm, reddish-brown to blackish. 2n = 30.{\i  Limestone rocks and screes, }1700-1850{\i  m. S. Greece} ({\i Chelmos Oros}). Gr. ({\i W. & C. Anatolia.})
