\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs. Inflorescence paniculate to capitate. Bracts present or absent. Calyx 5-toothed, 5- to 15-veined with scarious commissures. Petals 5, exceeding the calyx, with or without claw; coronal scales absent. Stamens 10; styles 2. Capsule dehiscing with 4 teeth. Seeds dorsiventrally compressed; embryo straight. (Incl.{\i  Tunica} auct.,{\i  Kohlrauschia }Kunth.)
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28 It is not practicable to make a clear distinction, as is done in{\i  Dianthus}, between epicalyx-scales and bracts. The term 'bract' is therefore used to cover both.
\par 

